# fourth-arm-substrate-carriers.form - substrate carriers on the emitted fourth kernel (fkwu)
#
# Why this cell exists: the per-band "what crossed and why" floor used to live as
# free prose in the fourth-arm-bands.txt header, where concurrent rebases kept
# dropping it. The manifest rows are the proof; this STRUCTURED cell is the
# durable floor/north-star/gate for the substrate-carrier arc, so the story is
# read from tokens (append-friendly, per-arc, low rebase pressure), not prose.

(fourth-arm-substrate-carriers
  (north-star
    (sentence "The content-addressed substrate is durable through one Form storage-port contract: memory and segmented-FILE stay in the pure deterministic four-way floor, while Postgres becomes first-class at the host carrier boundary with rollback-safe native evidence, so content-addressing survives a process and persistence boundary without pretending the pure fourth kernel contains a database engine.")
    (connected-tissue "Harmonizes with form/fourth-arm-bands.txt (the floor source for four-way coverage), hati-os.form (the kernel surface), the native executor proof ledger, and commit evidence so the sister nodes name one current floor and one next gap.")
    (must-carry content-addressed-intern durable-named-cells memory-carrier file-carrier postgres-carrier effect-once-let single-walk-comparison sequenced-effects native-host-io native-text-write native-file-append)
    (proof-shape same-shape-same-nodeid durable-content-key-roundtrip four-way-0-divergent rollback-safe-host-carrier-receipt))

  (floor
    (sentence "A durable-carrier claim is allowed only when the band crosses four-way on fkwu with 0 divergence and its remaining gate is named; a divergence is never buried by leaving the band out of the manifest.")
    (no-silent-zero unsupported-lowering-must-not-be-a-valid-table)
    (current-supported
      content-address-intern_node-tag-47        # same (category,children) -> same NodeID via live-table dedup, the C image of the Go byHash
      node_eq-tag-80-structural                 # node equality reads as structural identity
      trivial-intern-dedup-tags-43-46           # same value -> same trivial cell, so let-inlining re-walks stay bounded
      durable-substrate-core-memory-carrier     # intern + named cells + equivalence durable over the functional assoc-list carrier (band substrate-core)
      sequenced-bare-do-tag-69                  # bare do-statements fire exactly once in order (band do-effect-seq)
      single-walk-eq-lt-tags-102-103            # eq/lt evaluate each operand exactly once (band eq-effect-once)
      host-io-temp_dir-tag-101                  # $TMPDIR resolution as a native arm
      host-io-fs-carriers-tags-55-63            # open/read/write/close/lseek/mkdir/rmdir/unlink/rename/size/append/slice
      host-io-real-roundtrip                    # real filesystem write -> read crosses four-way deterministically (band hostio-roundtrip)
      host-io-file-mtime-scan-run               # real file freshness plus string scan stride (band hostio-observation)
      jit-scan-run-helper-value-abi             # scan_run inside a JIT helper path (band go-jit-value-helper)
      native-write-file-text-tag-104            # overwrite/truncate text write floor (band write-file-text)
      native-file-append                        # append log write floor (band file-append)
      segmented-file-carrier-four-way           # storage-port memory/file substitutability and durability (band storage-port)
      graph-node-port-four-way                  # graph-node port shape over storage carriers (band graph-node-port)
      graph-node-memory-mutation-carrier        # graph mutation over memory carrier (band graph-node-mutation-memory-carrier)
      graph-node-file-carrier-reopen            # file carrier reopen proof (band graph-node-mutation-file-carrier)
      graph-node-full-mutation-verdict          # memory/file agreement and full file mutation verdict (bands graph-node-mutation-carrier, graph-node-mutation-file-verdict)
      ideas-graph-file-projection               # idea response projection over reopened file stores (band ideas-graph-projection)
      postgres-carrier-boundary-receipt)        # storage-port-all-carriers over throwaway Postgres, verdict 111111
    (current-unsupported
      broader-source-scan-recipes))             # remaining host-io lift after scan_run/file_mtime

  (next-step
    (sentence "With the bounded Postgres carrier receipt landed, broader source-scan recipes can now build on the scan_run and file_mtime floor.")
    (gate broader-source-scan-recipes)
    (why "Statement-level effects already fire once (sequenced bare-do, tag 69), operand-level effects already fire once (single-walk eq/lt, tags 102/103), nested do-lets snapshot effecting values, the minimum write floor includes write_file_text plus append, storage-port proves memory/file substitutability with durability, full graph mutation crosses over the file carrier, ideas projection crosses over reopened file stores, host-io freshness/scan observation now crosses through file_mtime plus scan_run, and storage-port-all-carriers proves the same storage-test verdict across memory, segmented-file, and throwaway Postgres. The Postgres proof remains a host-carrier boundary receipt, not a database engine inside fkwu.")))
